y Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"CRAON","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon): unexplained."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Maurice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Late Latin name <i>Mauricius</i>, a derivative of <i>Maurus</i> (a byname meaning ‘Moor’, i.e. ‘dark, swarthy’), borne by, among others, an early Byzantine emperor (  <i>c.</i>539–602 ). It was introduced to Britain by the Normans and was popular in the Middle English period, but was not widely adopted by the nobility and became rare in the 17th century. Between the mid-19th century and the 1940s, it was moderately popular but has since faded again.  See also  Morris ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maurice V de CRAON was born about 1239, in Craon, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France, his father, Maurice IV de Craon, was 27 and his mother, Jeanne de ROCHEFORT, was 26. He married Mahaut Berthout de Malines de Mechelen in January 1276. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 4 March 1282, in Paris, Île-de-France, France, at the age of 44."},"et":{"ABT 1239–4 MAR 1282":"umbes 1239–4. märts 1282","1239–1282":"1239–1282","1255–1306":"1255–1306","1279–1333":"1279–1333","1282–1322":"1282–1322","1213–1250":"1213–1250",